subSubSection.paragraph:
In life (Fig. 
5
), dorsal surface reddish brown; horny spinules on the skin white; pineal ocellus yellowish; a yellowish mid-dorsal stripe on the posterior dorsum; dorsolateral fold dark brown; upper flank dark brown; lower flank light brown; suprabrachial gland light brown. Dorsal forelimbs light brown; a longitudinal black stripe on the anterior surface of the forelimb; dorsal hindlimbs dark brown, four dark crossbars on the thigh, three on the tibia and three on the tarsus. Loreal and temporal regions dark brown, tympanum light brown; upper ⅓ iris brownish white and lower ⅔ iris reddish brown; maxillary gland and shoulder gland white. Throat dark purplish brown; ventral surface of body and limbs creamy white; rear thigh tinged with pink; ventral hand white with large purplish brown patches; ventral foot purplish brown.

In preservative (Fig. 
6
), dorsal surface faded with the pineal ocellus and mid-dorsal stripe clearer; white spinules more distinct; dorsal limbs faded with the crossbars more distinct; ventral surface faded, throat grey.

